Jenna Etheridge, News24(File, Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A Cape Town metro police officer is in a critical but stable condition after being shot at eight times while in his vehicle, a City official said on Monday.Constable Mqondisi Mkhontwana was on his way home from Mandalay on Sunday night when he was ambushed at an intersection in Mitchells Plain, said safety and security mayoral committee member JP Smith.The shots went through the right-hand side of the vehicle. Three bullets hit the officer.Smith said the officer was in a critical, but stable condition after an emergency operation."We call on anyone with information to come forward," he urged.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.